cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.CV. 

This paper deals with a data structure for nearest neighbor queries in a polygon, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The data structure is dynamic, meaning it supports insertions and deletions, which suggests it belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) category. The problem of finding the nearest neighbor can also be seen as a search problem, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of geodesic distances suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR), where such distances are commonly used.
